### Copy a droplet

```
Definition
```

```http
POST /v3/droplets/:guid/copy HTTP/1.1
```

```
Example Request
```

```shell
curl "https://api.example.org/v3/droplets/[guid]/copy" \
  -X POST \
  -H "Authorization: bearer [token]" \
  -H "Content-type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "relationships": {
      "app": {
        "guid": "[app-guid]"
      }
    }
  }'
```

```
Example Response
```

```http
HTTP/1.1 201 Created
Content-Type: application/json

<%= yield_content :single_copied_staging_buildpack_droplet %>
```

Copy a droplet to a different app. The copied droplet excludes the
environment variables listed on the source droplet.

#### Query Parameters

Name | Type | Description
---- | ---- | ------------
**guid** | _uuid_ | Source guid of the droplet to be copied.
